\subsection*{6.7.1 Mastoiditis}

Mastoiditis is a bacterial infection of the mastoid bone behind the ear. Without treatment it can lead to meningitis and brain abscess.

\section*{Diagnosis}

Key diagnostic features are:
high fever
tender swelling behind the ear.

\section*{Treatment}
- Give IV or IM cloxacillin or flucloxacillin at $50 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg}$ every 6 h or ceftriaxone until the child improves, for a total course of 10 days.
If there is no response to treatment within 48 h or the child's

