\section*{6．7．2 Acute otitis media}

\section*{Diagnosis}

This is based on a history of ear pain or pus draining from the ear（for＜ 2 weeks）． On examination，confirm acute otitis media by otoscopy．The ear－drum will be red，inflamed，bulging and opaque，or perforated with discharge．

